{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/kxucy5","slide":2,"text":"The decision problem is not simply detecting a geopolitical event. It is compressing the time it takes to turn an uncertain signal into an action a procurement leader can defend. Our current simulated Hormuz fixture makes the stakes tangible: 1.2 million barrels per day of supply impact at the median, 48.2 million dollars of additional import cost per day, over a visible 21-day assumption. These are not live forecasts; they are deliberately labeled scenario outputs. The product attacks the decision bottleneck itself."}
