{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/10fetcfa","slide":3,"text":"The system never turns a raw signal directly into a purchase order.","textPreview":"The system never turns a raw signal directly into a purchase order.","textChars":67,"textLines":1,"bbox":[225,534,760,38]}
{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/3r5z5o","slide":3,"text":"This is the product in one line. A user enters a source-labeled signal. Gemini structures it. The backend resolves only entities that exist in the seeded network and computes an explainable corridor score. Then the workflow stops. An analyst reviews and confirms the scenario assumptions before Monte Carlo simulation and constrained portfolio optimization run. The result is explained and finally recorded as a local human decision. Each stage is linked to the prior persisted output. There is no shortcut from alert to action."}
