{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/e8db9w","slide":4,"text":"The innovation here is not asking an LLM to pretend it understands supply procurement. Gemini has two bounded jobs: it turns unstructured text into a validated proposal, and it explains an already selected portfolio. The deterministic system owns the things that must be correct: entity resolution, risk scoring, Monte Carlo distributions, and OR-Tools constraints. The UI exposes confidence, assumptions, and unknowns rather than hiding them. And even after a recommendation is produced, human approval is required. That is meaningful AI: useful without becoming unaccountable."}
