{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/fi8nag","slide":7,"text":"These are the innovations judges should remember because they solve real adoption blockers. First, provenance cannot be spoofed: pasted input cannot call itself a live feed. Second, assumptions are not hidden inside a model; they are editable and stored with the scenario request, including a reproducibility seed. Third, the optimizer does not output one magical answer; it returns four clearly differentiated postures. Finally, the approval record is linked to the recommendation actually produced by the workflow. Each innovation combines implementation discipline with a practical business consequence: people can trust and govern the decision."}
