{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/x4z6l0vq","slide":9,"text":"Explicit deterministic fallback when Gemini is unavailable.","textPreview":"Explicit deterministic fallback when Gemini is unavailable.","textChars":59,"textLines":1,"bbox":[1025,537,140,42]}
{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/bavfgo","slide":9,"text":"Our strongest results are behavioral, because this is a decision-support product. The current suite has 22 passing backend tests. It protects six linked workflow stages, a default of one thousand reproducible scenario runs, and four constrained procurement portfolios. Crucially, it also tests failure modes: no execution without a known proposal, no fabricated corridor for unrelated text, escalation to maximum resilience when simulated economics demand it, and no external execution from approval. The product remains usable when Gemini is unavailable through an explicit deterministic fallback—not a silent degradation. This is reliability by design."}
